packages/docs/src/how-it-works.md
     5→# How It Works
     7→Enclosed is designed with a focus on security and privacy, ensuring that your notes remain confidential from creation to retrieval. This section explains the entire process, from creating a note to decrypting it, highlighting the end-to-end encryption that makes Enclosed a secure platform.
     8→
     9→## 1. Note Creation
    13→## 2. Key Generation
    17→## 3. Master Key Derivation
    21→## 4. Note Encryption
    25→## 5. Sending to Server
    29→## 6. Storage and ID Assignment
    33→## 7. Link Generation
    37→## 8. Link Sharing
    41→## 9. Note Retrieval
    45→## 10. Key Extraction
    49→## 11. Password Prompt (If Applicable)
    53→## 12. Master Key Derivation
    57→## 13. Note Decryption

packages/docs/src/index.md
     5→# Enclosed
     7→**Enclosed** is a minimalistic web application designed for sending private and secure notes. Whether you need to share sensitive information or just want a simple way to send encrypted messages, Enclosed provides a user-friendly interface with strong security features to ensure your data remains confidential.
     8→
     9→The name **Enclosed** is inspired by the idea of keeping your notes safe and secure, like a sealed envelope.
    10→
    11→## Key Features
    27→## Why Enclosed?
    33→## Get Started

packages/docs/src/integrations/cli.md
     1→# CLI Guide
     3→The Enclosed Command-Line Interface (CLI) allows you to create and manage secure notes directly from your terminal. This guide will walk you through installing the CLI, creating and viewing notes, and configuring the CLI for different use cases.
     4→
     5→## Installation
    29→## Creating a Note
    77→## Viewing a Note
